<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="264" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,440,152,179]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">Description. Colour.</emphasis>
Yellowish green. Frontoclypeus pale brown. Ocelli pale yellowish brown, margined with red brown. Eyes red brown, 1 white stripe medially margined with red brown line. Forewings transparent and veins pale in male. Hind wings hyaline, pale white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,261,287]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">Body.</emphasis>
Length: male 7.0 mm to tip of the forewing. Vertex rounded anteriorly, little upturned anteriorly. Ocellus close to corresponding eye. Measurements of vertex length: interocular width: pronotal length (mm) 0.83: 1.12: 0.83.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,719]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,378,368,395]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">Male genitalia:</emphasis>
Subgenital plates with 6 setae laterally. Pygofer side subtriangular apically. Aedeagus with pair of processes subapically, curving dorsally; in caudal view, shaft constricted at about 1/4, 1/2 and 3/4 of its length in dorsal/ventral view, keeled ventrally; gonopore subapical on ventral side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,719]" box="[199,418,477,503]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,477,503]" pageId="7" pageNumber="264">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
